UPDATE secondary_sources SET enriched_text = 'Concepts: s5(1)(b), s5(3), implied consent, lawful interests, s14(1) inadmissibility, clandestine recordings, admissibility challenge

Covers: legal framework and argument under the Listening Devices Act 1991 for admitting one-party recordings.

**TASMC** decision ***MOORE v HARRISON 2018*** (not published but saved in files)

**Legal Argument**

***Listening Devices Act 1991***

Section 5(1)(b) -- cannot record a conversation to which you are a party

If caught under 5(1)(b) it is inadmissible under s 14(1)

Exception to Section 5(1)(b) is contained in s 5(3)

5(3)(a) -- implied consent; or

**5(3)(b)(i) -- reasonably necessary for the protection of the lawful interests of that principal party**

