UPDATE secondary_sources SET enriched_text = 'Concepts: Moore v Harrison, victim''s sister recording, family violence, s5 LDA, s38 application, HH Magistrate Stanton

Covers: the Moore v Harrison decision and its factual context regarding a recording made by the victim''s sister.

Written decision of your Brother Magistrate Ken Stanton in the matter of ***Moore v Harrison \[2018\] TASMC*** in Launceston. Of I course I accept that this can be of guidance only, and that the Court is no way bound by this decision, but the reasoning and conclusions reached by HH magistrate Stanton in that decision inform my application to admit this evidence today.

Moore v Harrison concerned a recording made by the victim''s sister. That recording was said to contain evidence of recent complaint made the sister by the victim of an assault perpetrated by the defendant.

The victim was unaware that a recording was made of the conversation she had with her sister.

