UPDATE secondary_sources SET enriched_text = 'Concepts: prosecution burden, beyond reasonable doubt, Woolmington, proof of all elements, consent negated, s182(4) elements

The rule is that the Crown bears the onus of proof to establish each of the four conditions in s 182(4) beyond reasonable doubt; it is insufficient to prove only one or some of the listed elements. This principle is grounded in Woolmington v DPP [1935] AC 462 and was applied in Tasmanian analysis: the prosecution must satisfy the jury beyond reasonable doubt that (a) the act was otherwise unlawful, (b) injurious to the public, (c) injurious to the person assaulted, and (d) involved a breach of the peace. Only if the Crown discharges that burden will the existence of the victim’s consent be rendered ineffective as a defence.', enriched = 1 WHERE id = 'Criminal Code Act 1924 (Tas) s 182(4); Woolmington v DPP [1935] AC 462';
