UPDATE secondary_sources SET enriched_text = 'Concepts: delay mitigation, anxiety and stress, rehabilitation during delay, unnecessary delay, self-inflicted delay, Tasmanian authorities

Delay in prosecution can be a substantial mitigating factor in sentencing when it is unnecessary (longer than ordinarily required given the case complexity) or has resulted in anxiety and stress to the accused or demonstrable rehabilitation during the delay. Palmer v Tasmania [2024] TASCCA 6 summarises the two bases: (1) delay causes punitive anxiety/stress; (2) delay may evidence rehabilitation. Delay that is self-inflicted (absconding, evasion) and delay attributable to the accused reduces or negates mitigation credit. The decision aggregates earlier authorities explaining the limits and conditions under which delay is mitigatory.', enriched = 1 WHERE id = 'secondary-authority---r-v-km-2004-nswcca-65';
